-- Kafka basic Commands

Create a Topic : docker exec orderflow-kafka kafka-topics --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --describe --topic playground

Produce a  message  : docker exec -it orderflow-kafka kafka-console-producer --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --topic playground

Consume the   messages from beginning :  docker exec orderflow-kafka kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --topic playground --from-beginning --property print.partition=true --property print.offset=true --timeout-ms 5000

producer with key support : docker exec -it orderflow-kafka kafka-console-producer --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --topic playground --property "parse.key=true" --property "key.separator=:"


open consumer  with demo group 1 : docker exec -it orderflow-kafka kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --topic playground --group demo-group --property print.partition=true

open consumer  with group 2   : docker exec -it orderflow-kafka kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --topic playground --group another-group --property print.partition=true

Describe the  consumer  group :   docker exec orderflow-kafka kafka-consumer-groups --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --describe --group another-group

delete the Topic ( Playground )  :  docker exec orderflow-kafka kafka-topics --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --delete --topic playground

Verify the  deleted topic is gone : docker exec orderflow-kafka kafka-topics --bootstrap-server kafka:9092 --list